Report Name: MI212-01 - HISTORY REPORT
Report Description: History Report- Case Histroy Notes from MIS are populated on the report. Notes added by FASB in MIS do not show in ICM. FASB may need to also see Case Notes that go back historically prior to ICM Notes records. These are only available through MIS and are currently requested through an Ad Hoc Report. This report is not auto generated. Report and function is still required by FASB

Report Name: RMS To Gain Repayment Upload Error Report (MI10B-01)
Report Description: RMS report = Discrepancy in Debt amount between systems. FBM Project identified records between MIS and RMS that are mismatched. There is a current manual Reconcilliation completed quarterly. MIS recieves a file from RMS, runs a discrepancy report and provides cases that have Debt balance discrpancy to FASB for Manual Adjustment. This is is a known issues and has been identified the the Requirement for Successor system to RMS future state.

Report Name: BCCCU - EXRD (AMP)
Report Description:
Automated Transfer System Detailed Listing
Daily banking- what has been processed and returend with Central 1 the previous day through
ORS - Online Return System -
For On Demand Payment - Not Monthly Cheques
BCCCU reports come directly from Central 1 when the daily files are downloaded so we have no insight into the logic. There are similar reports for OD cheques that are also sent to R2W.
HMISJPJK carries out bank reconciliation processing and uses the DREC file to match cheque data from Central 1 to the MIS payment history DB2 tables and updates cashed cheque data.
Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

HMISJPJK carries out bank reconciliation processing and uses the DREC file to match cheque data from Central 1 to the MIS payment history DB2 tables and updates cashed cheque data.
Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

Report Name: BCCCU - EXRD
Report Description:
CUBC Online Returns Processed Items - Report from Daily Central 1 banking data 
Daily banking- what has been processed and returend with Central 1 the previous day through
ORS - Online Return System -
For Computer Cheques Only
List payments chashed on the day prior 
BCCCU reports come directly from Central 1 when the daily files are downloaded so we have no insight into the logic. There are similar reports for OD cheques that are also sent to R2W.
HMISJPJK carries out bank reconciliation processing and uses the DREC file to match cheque data from Central 1 to the MIS payment history DB2 tables and updates cashed cheque data.
Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

ORS - Online Return System -
For Computer Cheques Only
List payments chashed on the day prior 
BCCCU reports come directly from Central 1 when the daily files are downloaded so we have no insight into the logic. There are similar reports for OD cheques that are also sent to R2W.
HMISJPJK carries out bank reconciliation processing and uses the DREC file to match cheque data from Central 1 to the MIS payment history DB2 tables and updates cashed cheque data.
Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

HMISJPJK carries out bank reconciliation processing and uses the DREC file to match cheque data from Central 1 to the MIS payment history DB2 tables and updates cashed cheque data.
Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

Report Name: BCCCU MONTHLY STATEMENT (AMP)
Report Description:
Central 1 summary Statement 
BCCCU reports come directly from Central 1 when the daily files are downloaded so we have no insight into the logic. There are similar reports for OD cheques that are also sent to R2W.
HMISJPJK carries out bank reconciliation processing and uses the DREC file to match cheque data from Central 1 to the MIS payment history DB2 tables and updates cashed cheque data.
Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

Report Name: BCCCU Account Activity And Balances (AMP)
Report Description:
Central 1 activity and balances
BCCCU reports come directly from Central 1 when the daily files are downloaded so we have no insight into the logic. There are similar reports for OD cheques that are also sent to R2W.
HMISJPJK carries out bank reconciliation processing and uses the DREC file to match cheque data from Central 1 to the MIS payment history DB2 tables and updates cashed cheque data.
Mismatched records are reported in report MI92T-01. which is also produced by job JPJK. 
A discovery session with FASB and possibly Treasury would be required to provide more details on the logic

Report Name: Hardship and Transition Monitoring By Worker (MI177-01)
Report Description:
Case Management - Hardship
Report Sorted by Office number, then Hardship Type. Used to monitor cases where Hardship has exceeded maximum months as per policy 

Report Requirments 
Case Status Open
Case Hardship Type Not Null, then include case in report, 
populate Legacy File ID, KP Name, Harship Type, Hardship End Date, Count number of months H/S benefits issued. Sort by Hardship Type
